From Gary Keim Subject Re X Toolkits Excerpts from Apr X Toolkits Paul P I am getting Linux so I will have InterViews but I don't know how it will I get the impression Andrew is from the FSF but I don't know what it looks like If you're on the internet and your site isn't sheltered from external tcp ip traffic you can use the Remote Andrew Demo to see what the Andrew Toolkit looks like Remote Andrew Demo Service This network service allows you to run Andrew Toolkit applications without the overhead of obtaining or compiling the Andrew You need a host machine on the Internet and you need to be running the window A simple finger command will allow you to experience ATK applications You'll be able to compose multimedia documents navigate through the interactive Andrew Tour and use the Andrew Message System to browse through CMU's three thousand bulletin boards and To use the Remote Andrew Demo service simply run the following command on your machine finger The service will give you further Gary Keim Andrew Consortium